The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the second Ministerial to Advance Religious Freedom, addressing the issue of religious persecution around the world. He highlighted the importance of freedom of religion and faith in the United States, as well as the efforts made by the Trump administration to defend religious freedom both domestically and internationally. Pence also mentioned specific cases of religious persecution in countries such as Turkey, Venezuela, Iran, Burma, China, and North Korea. He called for the release of individuals who have been imprisoned for their religious beliefs and urged governments to respect the rights of conscience. Pence emphasized the need for solidarity and continued efforts to advance religious liberty globally.